1.title: But Africa Is... So Far!
1.plot: The kids think Jessie is going to Africa to find Brooks. They make the trip to the continent themselves, but then end up on an adventure.

2.title: A Close Shave
2.plot: Jessie's stepsister Darla comes to visit, and Jessie enlists Tony's help to try to cover up the fact she didn't go through with the wedding. Meanwhile, Luke shaves for the first time and when Bertram comes to help, things get a bit hairy.

3.title: Four Broke Kids
3.plot: The Ross family faces an unexpected dilemma when they find out their parents have lost all their money and must learn to live without it.

4.title: Moby and SCOBY
4.plot: Jessie goes back to college and ends up in the same class as Ravi. Meanwhile, Zuri brings home a baby giraffe from Africa, and Emma pranks Luke so he thinks he is going crazy.

5.title: Karate Kid-tastrophe
5.plot: Jessie finds herself in unfamiliar territory when Emma's unexpected behavior gets her into trouble at school. Meanwhile, Luke takes on the role of Sensei to train Zuri for her upcoming karate belt test.

6.title: Basket Case
6.plot: Eager to play in Luke's basketball game, Ravi unexpectedly runs into LA Clippers star Chris Paul, who he enlists to coach him. Meanwhile, Jessie learns that Hudson is her new classmate and is unhappily forced to partner with him for an assignment.

7.title: Capture the Nag
7.plot: When the kids are snowed in at the penthouse, an epic game of capture the flag ensues. Allegiances are tested, tricks are pulled and everyone goes a little overboard.

8.title: What a Steal
8.plot: In an effort to help Ravi make friends, Jessie takes him to a MENSA meeting in the park. However, their new friends, Madeline and Scott, may be too good to be true.

9.title: Driving Miss Crazy
9.plot: Emma wants her license, so Jessie teaches her how to drive. Ravi and Luke accidentally break one of Zuri's games, forcing a stand-off.

10.title: Bye Bye Bertie
10.plot: Bertram has had enough, so decides to quit and to go work for Mrs. Chesterfield. Meanwhile, the Ross family hires a new butler, Roger, who takes his job very seriously.

11.title: Rossed at Sea: Part 1
11.plot: While on vacation, the Ross family finds a girl stranded in the middle of the ocean and invites her aboard their yacht. Meanwhile, Bertram stays home and babysits Mrs. Kipling, who has separation anxiety from Ravi.

12.title: Rossed at Sea: Part 2
12.plot: While exploring an Italian island, the Ross family's tour guide tells a story about Jessie's necklace, and how its curse brings anyone who wears it bad luck in love.

13.title: Rossed at Sea: Part 3
13.plot: In the final part of the "Rossed at Sea" three-parter, Jessie abruptly ends the Ross family vacation because the kids are constantly fighting. They wind up in a pickle when they find the yacht the next morning floating in the middle of the sea with no captain or crew in sight.

14.title: Dance, Dance, Resolution
14.plot: It's school dance time, and the Ross family pulls out all of the stops to score dates. Meanwhile, Jessie helps Bertram prepare for his first solo at the Metropolitan Opera.

15.title: Someone Has Tou-Pay
15.plot: Bertram's new toupee that he bought for his band's big performance has gone missing, so Jessie interrogates each of the kids in hopes to find it.

16.title: Identity Thieves
16.plot: When Luke becomes the brain of the family and Zuri the new trendy fashions, Ravi and Emma feel their identities have been stolen. Meanwhile, Bertram wonders what might be behind the only door in the penthouse he hasn't opened.

17.title: Katch Kipling
17.plot: When Mrs. Kipling becomes a celebrity, it puts a strain on her relationship with Ravi. Meanwhile, Bertram preps Emma for an audition and Zuri tries to be more independent.

18.title: The Ghostest with the Mostest
18.plot: When Jessie makes the Ross kids bring Stuart along for trick-or-treat he tells them a haunting story about Abigail, a ghost who is out to get them. One by one, the kids mysteriously disappear.

19.title: The Fear in Our Stars
19.plot: Jessie has to relearn all the "special skills" she listed on her resume for a commercial that she booked. Meanwhile, Ravi convinces Luke that a meteor is headed towards Earth.

20.title: Jessie Goes to Hollywood
20.plot: In the series finale, when Christina Ross returns home, Jessie heads to L.A. for a role in a movie. But when the kids realize that they still need her, they follow Jessie to Hollywood.

1.title: New York, New Nanny
1.plot: Jessie Prescott is an 18-year-old teenage girl who moves to New York to live on her own. Once she arrives, she incidentally accepts an offer to become the nanny of a high flying couple's four kids.

2.title: The Talented Mr. Kipling
2.plot: Jessie comes to the rescue when the condominium owner wants Ravi's pet lizard Mr. Kipling out of the building. Zuri brings home another imaginary friend and Luke and Emma work together in a school photo class project.

3.title: Used Karma
3.plot: After Jessie accepts a date to go on lunch with Tony, Emma gives her dating advice from teen magazines. Ravi becomes the target of Luke's practical jokes.

4.title: Zombie Tea Party 5
4.plot: Jessie teams up with Luke to beat the paintball rival who wins every year. Meanwhile, Zuri plans a tea party and Emma is invited and promptly uninvited by her best friends to Fashion Week.

5.title: One Day Wonders
5.plot: Jessie gets her big break when a music producer spots her singing a song she wrote. Emma helps Bertram look good for his social network profile photo.

6.title: Zuri's New Old Friend
6.plot: Jessie wants Zuri to play with real friends instead of imaginary ones, but when Zuri befriends the much older Nana Bananas - who wears yellow track suits, talks to her late husband named Harold in the park, and constantly squeaks a yellow horn when she makes jokes, Jessie is worried. Meanwhile, Ravi thinks that Mr. Kipling has found true love with a playground dinosaur.

7.title: Creepy Connie Comes a Callin'
7.plot: Jessie hires a new tutor for Luke but it turns out that the tutor has a huge crush on Luke. Meanwhile Ravi downloads an app that predicts the future and fears that Bertram will be endangered.

8.title: Christmas Story
8.plot: When Morgan and Christina get stuck in a snowstorm, the family fears they won't make it home in time for Christmas and Jessie is left with shopping for the kid's Christmas presents. When Jessie takes the kids to the mall to see Santa, they have a run-in with his mischievous elves.

9.title: Star Wars
9.plot: Morgan has decided to put Jordan Taylor in his next movie but Jordan will only do it if no one knows that Jordan is at their house and if the family respects him. It causes chaos when Emma gets jealous when Jordan asks Jessie out then tells the whole world about it, Ravi tries to prove about acting to Jordan, and Luke and Zuri keeps prank calling the people in Jordan's phone. Meanwhile, Bertram tries to work hard to get a week off.

10.title: Are You Cooler Than a 5th Grader

11.title: Take the A-Train... I Think!
11.plot: Jessie and the Ross kids struggle to navigate the New York City Subway system, while the grounded Luke teams up with Bertram to defeat a spider.

12.title: Romancing the Crone
12.plot: Jessie and Zuri sneak into Mrs. Chesterfield's apartment.

13.title: The Princess & the Pea Brain
13.plot: Jessie and Zuri read a bedtime story.

14.title: World Wide Web of Lies
14.plot: Jessie is bullied by a bossy nanny and ends up on her website.

15.title: The Kid Whisperer
15.plot: Jessie asks another nanny for advice.

16.title: Glue Dunnit: A Sticky Situation
16.plot: Ms. Chesterfield's shampoo is swapped with glue.

17.title: Badfellas
17.plot: Jessie doesn't approve of a boy Emma likes.

18.title: Beauty and the Beasts
18.plot: Zuri enters the Little Miss Big Apple Pageant.

19.title: Evil Times Two
19.plot: Nanny Agatha's twin sister Angela arrives from England, and seems to be the opposite of everything Agatha is, until Jessie begins to suspect that the girl is trying to steal the kids and Tony from her. Elsewhere, Emma is horrified to find a massive pimple on her nose.

20.title: Tempest in a Teacup
20.plot: Emma and Zuri hear recreate Jessie's prom on the terrace.

21.title: A Doll's Outhouse
21.plot: Zuri refuses to sleep in her room.

22.title: We Are So Grounded
22.plot: Jessie and the kids fly off to meet the parents in a private jet.

23.title: Creepy Connie's Curtain Call
23.plot: Jessie directs a play she's written at the kids' school.

24.title: Cattle Calls & Scary Walls
24.plot: Jessie decides she wants to try acting and plans on auditioning for a show.

25.title: Gotcha Day
25.plot: Jessie is in charge of 'Gotcha Day.'

26.title: The Secret Life of Mr. Kipling
26.plot: Ravi notices odd behavior from Mr. Kipling.

1.title: The Whining
1.plot: The kids learn the legend of the nanny who did "something terrible."

2.title: Green-Eyed Monsters
2.plot: Jessie becomes concerned about Tony's jealousy issues.

3.title: Make New Friends, But Hide the Old
3.plot: Emma meets a tough transfer student named Rosie.

4.title: 101 Lizards
4.plot: Ravi decides he wants to find good parents to adopt Ms. Kipling's babies.

5.title: Trashin' Fashion
5.plot: Emma is excited over an upcoming fashion show organized by the Ross family matriarch, but chaos ensues when the rest of the kids get involved.

6.title: Nanny in Miami
6.plot: After helping Austin Moon get his New Years' Eve performance at Times Square, Jessie and the Ross kids are invited to a concert in the Mall of Miami in which she writes her own song, and gets to perform a duet with Austin, who is also trying to deal with the advances of Emma. However, Jessie's lyrics turn out to have been written by Zuri, a fact she tries desperately to conceal from her.

7.title: Trouble with Tessie
7.plot: Jessie agrees to let Zuri bring her classroom pet bunny home.

8.title: Say Yes to the Messy Dress
8.plot: NBA player Chris Bosh needs somewhere to stay!

9.title: Teacher's Pest
9.plot: Jessie decides to volunteer in Zuri's classroom.

10.title: Jessie's Big Break
10.plot: Jessie gets her big break as a stunt double to popular Australian actress Shaylee Michaels.

11.title: Pain in the Rear Window
11.plot: Luke shows Jessie some dance moves but he trips and hurts his knee.

12.title: Toy Con
12.plot: Jessie passes along a cherished doll she had as a child to Zuri, but a sleazy auctioneer talks her into trading it in for a mechanical bunny doll with debatable taste. Meanwhile Luke and Emma set Bertram up with a chef he's head over heels in love with, only to find himself over his head when he has to learn how to salsa dance with her.

13.title: To Be or Not to Be
13.plot: Jessie and Zuri, Emma and Luke, and Ravi and Bertram all switch personalities.

14.title: Why Do Foils Fall in Love
14.plot: Jessie's anniversary gift to Tony is a song.

15.title: Kids Don't Wanna Be Shunned
15.plot: Emma is upset when her friends stand up for the new girl in school. Meanwhile, Luke decides to write a report on India, but makes Ravi do all the work for him.

16.title: All the Knight Moves
16.plot: Jessie discovers Zuri is a chess prodigy.

17.title: We Don't Need No Stinkin' Badges
17.plot: Jessie wants to prove that she is a great girl scout leader by helping Zuri earn a badge - which proves to be a hard quest. Meanwhile, Ravi's lies puts Bertram in a battle with his arch rival butler.

18.title: Somebunny's in Trouble
18.plot: Jessie loses a bunny that Zuri brings home as a class pet, and she struggles to keep it from Zuri until she finds it. Meanwhile, Emma starts to date a guy who likes sports. Luke is supposed to help her, only to end up "stealing" her date.

19.title: Punched Dumped Love
19.plot: Jessie punishes Emma by not letting her go to the school dance. However, Emma still sneaks out to warn Luke about his date's mean and jealous ex-boyfriend. Meanwhile, Ravi and Zuri set up traps all over the penthouse to prevent burglars.

20.title: Quitting Cold Koala
20.plot: Luke decides that it's time to cut the strings between him and Kenny the koala, with some help from Jessie, but it proves to be quite the challenge. Meanwhile, Stuart comes over to stay for a few days, and reveals a newfound crush on Emma.

21.title: Panic Attack Room
21.plot: While Jessie prepares for a big audition for Emma and Bertram's favorite show, everyone gets trapped in the penthouse panic room.

22.title: Throw Momma from the Terrace
22.plot: Jesse invites Bertram's mom to visit as a surprise for his birthday but Bertram and his mom do not get along; Ravi and Luke compete in a school egg-drop competition.

23.title: The Jessie-nator: Grudgement Day
23.plot: Jessie is visited by a middle-aged version of herself who arrives from the future to warn her of an army of robot Bertrams invented by Ravi that are seeking to destroy her and take over the world.

24.title: Diary of a Mad Newswoman
24.plot: Things become tense when Bryn joins the morning announcements and tries to force Emma, Luke and Ravi off the show. Meanwhile, Jessie tries to teach Zuri a lesson after reading her diary.

25.title: Break-Up and Shape-Up
25.plot: Jessie becomes suspicious of Tony when he trains a beautiful girl to be the new door-person. Things heat up even more when Jessie's hot ex-boyfriend comes to town. Meanwhile, Luke and Ravi fight on how to best reduce Bertram's stress level.

26.title: G.I. Jessie
26.plot: Jessie and the kids travel to her dad's military base in Texas. While there, she tries to convince her father that she made the right choice by moving to New York, but neither she, the kids nor old family feuds are making it easy for her.

1.title: Ghost Bummers
1.plot: Jessie and the kids are excluded from the building Halloween party. They throw their own party, which is interrupted when Emma and Luke become possessed by evil spirits.

2.title: Caught Purple Handed
2.plot: Jessie's new agent gets her a job as a hand model.

3.title: Understudied & Overdone
3.plot: Jessie gets an opportunity to be the understudy in an off-Broadway play. Unbeknownst to her, Luke plots to sabotage the star so Jessie gets to be on stage. Meanwhile, Emma and Zuri help Bertram make a web show in which he is the star.

4.title: The Blind Date, the Cheapskate, and the Primate
4.plot: To prove to Zuri that she's over Tony, Jessie decides that she and Tony will set each other up. Meanwhile, Ravi gets an internship at an animal shelter, and tries to prove worthy of the owner's trust whenever left in charge.

5.title: Lizard Scales and Wrestling Tales
5.plot: Luke becomes curious about the identities of his biological parents, and starts to investigate with Emma's help after Jessie refuses. However, things don't turn out the way he expected. Meanwhile, Ravi runs for reptile club president.

6.title: The Rosses Get Real
6.plot: Jessie is excited when she and the Ross kids are invited to participate in a reality show.

7.title: Good Luck Jessie: New York City Christmas
7.plot: After Teddy and PJ run into Jessie in New York, they encounter complete chaos at the Ross house.

8.title: Krumping and Crushing
8.plot: Jessie enrolls Luke in a dance class, and to Jessie's dismay, he decides to replace doing homework with dance practice. Meanwhile, Emma and Ravi thinks Zuri have a crush on Tony, and don't know what to do about it.

9.title: Hoedown Showdown
9.plot: When a new girl moves into the building, Jessie asks Emma to invite her to her party as a welcoming gesture.

10.title: Snack Attack
10.plot: Jessie hooks Zuri up with a new girl named Wendy McMillan after seeing a director to get her acting career started. With Jessie she's an angel, but while Bertram is in charge, she tears up the place and wrecks everything. Bertram tries to take care of it, but Wendy hooks Bertram up too. Zuri tells Jessie she's a monster and wants to stop playing with her. Meanwhile, Emma goes over her limit on her cell phone bill, so Jessie forces her to get a job so she can pay the bill herself.

11.title: Creepy Connie 3: The Creepening
11.plot: Connie returns, this time with her boarding school roommate Mackenzie, who appears even crazier than her. When she obsesses over Luke, Connie surprisingly defends him. But things may not be as they seem. Meanwhile, Emma gets fired from her job.

12.title: Acting with the Frenemy
12.plot: Jessie makes a friend in acting class only to find out her new pal Abbey is not all that she seems.

13.title: From the White House to Our House
13.plot: Jessie and Zuri set out to host a birthday party for Taylor, a new friend with a deployed member of the military. When Taylor decides she'd rather not celebrate anything without her mother, Zuri enlists the help of Mrs. Obama.

14.title: Help Not Wanted
14.plot: Jessie is in need of some extra money to buy a special gift for her dad's birthday. She accepts a job at Empire Skate Building only to find out that Emma is her boss. Luke, Ravi and Zuri do babysitting behind Jessie's back to earn money.

15.title: Where's Zuri?
15.plot: Jessie and Zuri discover Stuart has a new laid-back "manny" named Hudson. Having grown to like Stuart, Zuri resents being told not to see him, and they run off together. Emma, Luke and Bertram try to help Ravi prepare for a talent show.

16.title: Morning Rush
16.plot: A real-time countdown begins as Jessie races against the clock to insure the Ross kids get to school on time despite the countless obstacles that arise.

17.title: Lights, Camera, Distraction!
17.plot: Jessie becomes frustrated that she can't land any acting gigs, so she takes matters into her own hands by participating in a 24-hour film festival. She recruits the kids to help her direct, shoot and edit her film, but things get complicated when all the kids have their own ideas about what the film should be.

18.title: Spaced Out
18.plot: Ravi's birthday present from his parents is a trip to outer space with the rest of the Ross kids and Jessie. Their trip takes an unexpected turn when Ravi ends up not going.

19.title: The Telltale Duck
19.plot: Jessie agrees to accompany Bertram to his high school reunion, so he can show his former classmates how successful he has become. Meanwhile, Ravi steals a violent video game to be considered cool, only for his actions to haunt him.

20.title: Coffee Talk
20.plot: When Jessie lands two VIP wristbands to Emma and Zuri's dream concert, the girls compete to be her guest. Meanwhile, Bertram becomes infatuated with his new talking coffee maker.

21.title: Between the Swoon and New York City
21.plot: Jessie hits it off with a new guy she meets in the park named Brooks, unaware that he is Ms. Chesterfield's son. Meanwhile, Ravi and Luke fight about who has the right to a baseball Ravi catches at a Yankees game.

22.title: No Money, Mo' Problems
22.plot: Mrs. Chesterfield hires Bertram to dig up dirt on Jessie that would hopefully lead Brooks to break up with her.

23.title: The Runaway Bride of Frankenstein
23.plot: As the Ross kids prepare for the Halloween Festival, the festivities take a scary turn when Brooks proposes to Jessie, and she learns that none of the kids like him.

24.title: There Goes the Bride
24.plot: When Brooks lands a job in Africa and has to be there in two days, he and Jessie are forced to move up their wedding.

25.title: Ride to Riches
25.plot: Jessie is on a mission to get to an important audition; however, she and Ravi wind up on the "Rides to Riches" game show in which contestants can win prizes during their taxi ride. Emma and Luke follow Bertram to a renaissance faire.

26.title: Jessie's Aloha Holidays with Parker and Joey
26.plot: Parker and Joey, Jessie and the Ross kids plan a tropical Christmas at the family's Hawaiian villa where Jessie reunites with old friend and superstar, Shayelee Michaels.

locations: Hollywood Center Studios - 1040 N. Las Palmas Avenue, Hollywood, Los Angeles, California, USA::(all episodes)
imdb.plot outline: The series follows Jessie Prescott, a young woman from a small town with big dreams who, rebelling against her strict father, decides to leave the military base in Texas where she grew up and moves to New York City. She accepts a job as a nanny and moves into a multi-million dollar penthouse on the Upper West Side with the wealthy Ross family which includes: jet-setting parents, Morgan and Christina; and their four rambunctious children: Emma, Luke, Ravi and Zuri; along with the family pet (and Ravi's companion) Mr. (later Mrs.) Kipling, a 7 ft (2 m) Asian water monitor, that was later revealed to be a female. With a whole new world of experiences open to her, Jessie embarks on new adventures in the big city as she grows to rely on the love and support of the children in her care. Assisting her are Bertram, the family's sarcastic butler, and Tony, the building's 20-year-old doorman.
imdb.title: Jessie
plot: A Texan teen moves to New York City to follow her dreams and ends up as a nanny for a high profile couple's four children.::Anonymous

_Jessie_ (qv) Prescott (Debby Ryan) is a 19-year old teen from Texas who moves to the one area where she can actually become someone special- New York city. There, she lands into a job as a nanny to a married couple's kids, who are both movie directors. Left with no other choice, she accepts the offer and finds herself with 5 penthouse owners. Her troubles start with pretty, fashion-addicted, 13-year old, Emma Ross (Peyton List), freckle-faced but handsome player, 12-year old Luke Ross (Cameron Boyce), lizard-loving, Hindu outcast, 10-year old Ravi Ross (Karen Brar), chubby the bear and pony loving, 7-year old Zuri Ross (Skai Jackson), and lazy, sarcastic butler, Bertram (Kevin Chamberlin). _Jessie_ (qv) eventually learns to care for the new children, while somehow, start dating the hotel doorman, Tony
